━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

LOCATION: Security Hub, Deck 1 (Command Level)
STATUS: High Alert
ACCESS: GRANTED - SECURITY CLEARANCE VERIFIED

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The Security Hub sits at the heart of Helios Station's defenses. Dim blue
lighting preserves night vision while banks of monitors display traffic
patterns across every network segment. Chief Security Officer Adeyemi's
station dominates the center of the room.

"Networks are attack surfaces," her training materials begin. "Every
connection is a potential breach. Every open port is an invitation."

The solar flare disrupted more than communications. Without proper network
segmentation, a single compromised container could cascade through the
entire station. Adeyemi's defense-in-depth architecture is our best
protection - if we can verify it's still intact.

