SECURITY PRINCIPLES
═══════════════════

    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │                                                                     │
    │  1. LEAST PRIVILEGE                                                │
    │     Containers access only what they need. Nothing more.           │
    │                                                                     │
    │  2. DEFENSE IN DEPTH                                               │
    │     Multiple layers of protection. No single point of failure.    │
    │                                                                     │
    │  3. NETWORK SEGMENTATION                                           │
    │     Separate concerns into isolated zones. Limit blast radius.    │
    │                                                                     │
    │  4. VISIBILITY                                                     │
    │     Monitor traffic at boundaries. Detect anomalies early.        │
    │                                                                     │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

MODULE MISSIONS
═══════════════

    [1] isolation-verify    Verify Network Isolation Boundaries
    [2] segmentation        Design Secure Network Architecture
    [3] traffic-monitor     Inspect Cross-Network Traffic

